V4-5 changes/new features by AWE
1) added site (MK or CP) to calparams.  Made channel initialization site specific in tccMain (consolidated channels here)
   added checks for the existence of sa or cs to many locations to prevent errors.  This reduces channel access load on all
   RT systems because requests for dead (non-existent) channels causes a continuous sequence of UDP broadcasts.
   There are still a few orphan channels (inside the sad sa for example) ... these need to be pulled out and seperated.
2) Added automatic control of the M2 XY deadband.
3) Provide the option to keep loops closed when there is a STRAP timeout.


